<TITLE> BHF announces Asia Cup qualifiers squad with six new faces </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Hockey Federation Saturday announced a 16-member squad for this month's Asia Cup qualifiers picking five new players to the squad. The nine-nation qualifiers are scheduled for June 14 to 23 in Singapore as Bangladesh were drawn with hosts Singapore, Uzbekistan, Brunei and Chinese Taipei. Bangladesh will start the campaign taking on Brunei on the opening day. "We have picked the players considering performance in the recently concluded Premier Division Hockey League," Qumarul Islam Kismat, a selector of the four-member selection committee, told bdnews24.com. Kismat hopes the new players picked for the first time in the national squad will play their best in the qualifiers. The new players are goalkeeper Mehrab Hossain Kiron, Asaduzzaman Chadan, Ferdous Goldar, Sheikh Mohammad Nannu, Rimon Kumar and Krishna Kumar. Replying to a query, Kismat, who is also team manager, said that they dropped Abahani' skipper Ehsan Rana following his injury. Three players -- Jahid Bin Talib Shuvo, Tapash Barman and Iqbal Nader Prince --have been kept as standby. Squad: Mahbubullah Chowdhury Shakil, Mehrab Hossain Kiron, Mamunur Rahman Chayan, Isa Mia, Asaduzzaman Chandan, Moshiur Rahman Biplob, Ferdous Goldar, Shahidullah Titu, Musa Mia, Khandoker Hasan Ahmed, Sheikh M Nannu, Maksudul Alam Habul, Russel Mahmud Jimmy, Jahidul Islam Rajon, Rimon Kumar Ghosh and Krishna Kumar. Officials: Qumrul Islam Kismot (manager), Shahidullah Dolan (asst manager), Mahbub Harun (coach), Barkatullah Chapal (asst coach), Mirza Farid Ahmed (Judge) and Mahbubul Haq Mitu (Umpire). 
